        "title": "refactor: store Zalo hosted media in plugin state",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move Zalo hosted outbound media from temp JSON/bin sidecars into SQLite-backed plugin state.\n- Add a shared `openclaw/plugin-sdk/outbound-media` hosted-media store for metadata, chunk rows, expiry cleanup, rollback, and capacity pruning.\n- Update Zalo tests/docs/API baseline, plus a one-line unrelated extension lint fix required by `check:changed`.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/outbound-media.test.ts extensions/zalo/src/outbound-media.test.ts extensions/zalo/src/monitor.polling.media-reply.test.ts`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` -> clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- `pnpm check:changed` via Blacksmith Testbox: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/actions/runs/27078772885\n\n## Notes\n\nHosted media expiry is helper-owned rather than plugin-state TTL-owned so cleanup can delete metadata and chunk rows together. The helper prunes whole hosted entries before chunk row capacity can evict chunks independently.\n",
